The eastern road network's cargo is Midgaard's primary connection to oasis settlements and pyramid-adjacent communities; Burn Ledger records are central to trade monitoring.
The Water Court's jurisdiction over emergency reallocation claims predates Midgaard's charter; Midgaard's legal system incorporates Water Court decisions under "established corridor precedent" rather than competing jurisdiction.
Midgaard's Charter Sovereignty office has never challenged Water Court jurisdiction, recognizing its track record — centuries of kiln-sealed evidence — is more robust than Midgaard's charter for the same corridor.
The Continuity faction's favorable view of the Burn Ledger is unusual; the exception reflects that eastern trade depends on the Water Court functioning.

