The Courier Lantern Office's archive of eastern road manifests includes Burn Ledger ceramic tablet entries filed through Kowloon's northern trade route; goods traveling from eastern desert to northern delta move through multiple jurisdictions, and the Burn Ledger entry is the record that persists across all of them.
Kowloon's Jade Magistracy views the Water Court's Reed Law emergency reallocation framework as functionally equivalent to Kowloon's own crisis-rationing protocols — different institutional vocabulary for the same practical arrangement.

